## Data — Lewis & Short Lexicon & Morpheus Morphology (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The Lewis & Short lexicon data and Morpheus morphology database
(`data/ls.db`, `data/morph.db`) are licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Attribution:** Charlton T. Lewis and Charles Short, *A Latin Dictionary*
(1879), and Morpheus morphological analyzer, via the Perseus Digital
Library / Perseids project. Same source data as the companion
[`latin-mac`](https://github.com/Josolon/latin-mac) project — see that
repo for full sourcing detail.

---

## English-Icelandic Bridge Glossary (Creative Commons Attribution 4.0)

The `data/IS-EN_glossary.tsv` bridge glossary is licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

**Attribution:** English-Icelandic/Icelandic-English glossary 21.09,
compiled by Steinþór Steingrímsson, Luke James Obrien, Finnur Ágúst
Ingimundarson, Árni Davíð Magnússon, Þórdís Dröfn Andrésdóttir, and Inga
Guðrún Eiríksdóttir — The Árni Magnússon Institute for Icelandic Studies /
Reykjavik University, via CLARIN Iceland.
https://repository.clarin.is/repository/xmlui/handle/20.500.12537/144

---

## Icelandic Target-Word Morphology — BÍN (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The generated Icelandic morphology data (`data/is_noun_declension.tsv`,
`data/is_verb_forms.tsv`, `data/is_adj_declension.tsv`,
`data/is_adj_form_lemma.tsv`) is derived from BÍN and licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Attribution:** BÍN (Beygingarlýsing íslensks nútímamáls / Database of
Modern Icelandic Inflection), compiled by Kristín Bjarnadóttir at the Árni
Magnússon Institute for Icelandic Studies, via CLARIN Iceland.
https://repository.clarin.is/repository/xmlui/handle/20.500.12537/5
Accessed via the `islenska` PyPI package (Miðeind ehf., MIT-licensed code
wrapping the same BÍN data).

---

## Generated Icelandic Glossary & Reverse Index (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)

The generated Icelandic glossary (`data/ls_is.db`) and the reverse
(Icelandic → Latin) index derived from it are licensed under:

**Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International**
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

This follows from combining CC BY-SA 4.0 Lewis & Short data with the CC BY
4.0 bridge glossary — the ShareAlike term of the stricter license carries
through to the combined work.

---

## Summary

When distributing this dictionary:
1. Include/reference these licenses.
2. Keep the Perseus attribution (for Lewis & Short / Morpheus) and the
   CLARIN Iceland attribution (for the bridge glossary) intact.
3. Any derivative works using the Lewis & Short data or the generated
   Icelandic glossary must also be CC BY-SA 4.0.
